quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  55,1,"The Most Gracious (Allâh)!"
  55,2,"He has taught (you mankind) the Qur’ân (by His Mercy)."
  55,3,"He created man."
  55,4,"He taught him eloquent speech."
  55,5,"The sun and the moon run on their fixed courses (exactly) calculated with measured out stages for each (for reckoning)."
  55,6,"And the herbs (or stars) and the trees both prostrate themselves (to Allah - See V.22:18) (Tafsir Ibn Kathir)"
  55,7,"And the heaven: He has raised it high, and He has set up the Balance."
  55,8,"In order that you may not transgress (due) balance."
  55,9,"And observe the weight with equity and do not make the balance deficient."
  55,10,"And the earth: He has put down (laid) for the creatures."